            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I think it shouldn't create the kind of wrapped text shown above.\n\nThe \"weird\" wrapping is because of 'breakindent' (which I added in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/30695 ). That's tradeoff but disabling it would only change where the text is wrapped to...\n\n> If I add `wrap = false`, then the window is too small for the text\n\nThe float dimensions are decided by Nvim based on the window you opened it from (and the total space available to Nvim). Your screenshot doesn't show the surrounding layout, so we can only guess whether the dimensions were decided correctly in this case.",
