            "body": "Stumped into this problem as well since a long time ago. Here's just a simple example where the hover cuts off 2 characters at the width:\n\n<img width=\"404\" height=\"153\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b0e52873-5eed-4e07-a0c5-6f89f54015f3\" />\n\nJumping into the hover to scroll to the end of the line:\n\n<img width=\"390\" height=\"137\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/49d1853b-fd29-4205-8956-3574d76cd83a\" />\n\nI have no clue how I would be able to fix this in user-land, since setting `width`/`height` doesn't account for text length/paddings of the content. I'd rather not copy the whole built-in method to fix this tiny issue but is currently the only solution I can think of.",
